Name.label: Non-syndromic renal or urinary tract malformation
Non-syndromic urogenital tract malformation of male and female
Genetic non-syndromic renal or urinary tract malformation

TextSection.Contents: Duplication of the urethra is a rare congenital genitourinary anomaly, encompassing a wide spectrum of anatomic variants in which the urethra is partially or totally duplicated, which may be asymptomatic or cause symptoms such as incontinence, recurrent urinary infections and difficulty urinating.
